data.value:
A boxel is a cube of space containing procedurally generated star systems. Cube sizes depend on mass code: 'a' boxels are 10 ly across, 'h' boxels are 1280 ly.
Each boxel contains 8 children, arranged as 2 rows of 4 quadrants, each with their own generated star systems.
